{
  "texts": [
    "A-D Principle: If an action, φ, done by an agent can be described as a means by which that agent does something else, ψ, and ψ is intended by that agent (i.e., ψ-ing is an end or goal of φ-ing), then φ and ψ are the same action.",
    "On the face of it, the principle identifies what an agent does with everything they do by doing something else.",
    "So, we might think that in cases of offloading, an agent's",
    "Synthese (2025) 205:47",
    "act can be identified with the cognitive task(s) thereby performed."
  ]
}